<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-32-0853 </DOCNO><TEXT>An integrated local or regional energy supply concept should take accountof both central and decentralized energy conservation and supply strategies.The author makes a distinction between central heating systems for single-familybuildings on the one hand and district heating and gas on the other hand.The main elements of a decentralized supply strategy are listed: Cogenerationunits, cooperation between communities and industry, biomass conversioninto biogas, industrial waste heat recovery, and renewable energy sources(wind energy, solar energy). The advantages of decentralisation for thesupplier, the consumer, and the region are gone into, with particularregard to the occupational effects and the reduction of air pollution.(HWJ).</TEXT></DOC>